race.description: Department Of Fire & Emergency Services Maiden
race.comment: DASHING DIVA (11) wasn't far away at Northam two back before bumping into a dominant winner at Narrogin last time out when jumping an odds-on favourite. Happy to overlook one poor effort as she was trending the right way prior. Can bounce back to her best and land the knockout blow. SUMMER MOOD (7) was 2L off the winner last start over the 1107m journey here and looks poised for a bold effort third-up. Out to 1200m now where she turned in a strong performance to end last campaign. Maps to get a lovely run in transit and can make her presence felt. LOTSAMERIT (9) finished off strongly first-up over the 1107m journey and should appreciate the slight rise in trip. Draws to settle a touch closer this time around and can play a leading role. FLAMING DRAGON (2) is better than he showed last time out and can improve. CALEB (6) has won a trial at this track in readiness for his return and is not to be discounted.
